A re-recorded version of the song was released as a single to commemorate Matsu's tenth anniversary in music industry, to digital outlets like [[iTunes]], [[Mora (music store)|mora]], and also in [[KDDI|Chaku-Uta]] format, both as ringtone and the full song on March 21, 2007. The new version titled, {{nihongo|"Ashita, Haru ga Kitara 97<U+2013>07"|<U+660E><U+65E5><U+3001><U+6625><U+304C><U+6765><U+305F><U+3089> 97<U+2013>07}} was recorded at the Mouri Art Works Studio in [[Tokyo]].<ref name="nhk"/> Its modified lyrics penned by Y<U+016B>ji Sakamoto, the writer of the original song, are meant to convey the emotions of the singer ten years into her debut.<ref name="nat"/> In addition, Matsu's vocals from the original version are intermixed with the new vocals to contrast the difference between the current Matsu and the Matsu of ten years ago.<ref name="nat">{{cite web|url=http://natalie.mu/music/news/507|title=<nowiki>[<U+677E><U+305F><U+304B><U+5B50>]</nowiki> <U+65B0><U+66F2><U+3067>10<U+5E74><U+524D><U+306E><U+81EA><U+5206><U+3068><U+30C7><U+30E5><U+30A8><U+30C3><U+30C8>|trans_title=(Takako Matsu) Singing a duet with herself from 10 years ago in her new song|language=Japanese|date=March 2, 2007|publisher=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie]]|accessdate=May 5, 2014}}</ref> While talking to [[NHK]] at the time of the single's release, Matsu commented that the new lyrics not only reflect the changes she had made over the past 10 years, but also of Y<U+016B>ji Sakamoto.<ref name="nhk"/>

The new version, running 4 minutes and 54 seconds, was arranged by musician and future husband Yoshiyuki Sahashi.<ref name="yomu">{{cite web|url=http://www.yomiuri.co.jp/otona/hobby/artiste/20140527-OYT8T50146.html|script-title=ja:<U+677E><U+305F><U+304B><U+5B50> <U+300C><U+30A2><U+30CA><U+96EA><U+300D><U+3067><U+518D><U+30D6><U+30EC><U+30A4><U+30AF><U+306E><U+30D2><U+30DF><U+30C4>|trans_title=Takako Matsu: the secret of her second big break with ''Frozen''|work=[[The Yomiuri Shimbun]]|publisher=Yomiuri Group|date=May 30, 2014|language=Japanese|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6PyoyeS6l|archivedate=May 31, 2014|accessdate=May 31, 2014}}</ref><ref name="cherishlin">{{cite AV media notes|title=Cherish You|type=liner notes|others=[[Takako Matsu]]|publisher=[[Ariola Japan]]|id=BVCR-18096/7}}</ref> The song was included in her eighth studio album, ''Cherish You'' (2007).<ref name="apple">{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/jp/album/ming-ri-chunga-laitara-97/id217913014|title=iTunes - <U+30DF><U+30E5><U+30FC><U+30B8><U+30C3><U+30AF> - <U+677E><U+305F><U+304B><U+5B50><U+300C><U+660E><U+65E5><U+3001><U+6625><U+304C><U+6765><U+305F><U+3089> 97-07 - Single<U+300D>|publisher=itunes.apple.com|accessdate=May 3, 2014}}</ref><ref name="jbook">{{cite web|url=http://www.jbook.co.jp/p/p.aspx/3301585/s/|title=JBOOK<U+FF1A>Cherish You<U+FF1A><U+677E><U+305F><U+304B><U+5B50><U+FF1A>CD|publisher=J Book|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20140604092924/http://www.jbook.co.jp/p/p.aspx/3301585/s/ |archivedate=June 4, 2014 |accessdate=May 3, 2014}}</ref> and also on Matsu's compilation album, ''Footsteps: 10th Anniversary Complete Best'' (2008).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard-japan.com/goods/detail/307937|title=<U+677E><U+305F><U+304B><U+5B50> <U+300C>footsteps <U+FF5E>10th Anniversary Complete Best<U+FF5E><U+300D> {{!}} BVCR-18140/3|work=Billboard Japan|publisher=Hankyu Hanshin Holdings|language=Japanese|accessdate=May 31, 2014}}</ref> A TV commercial for the new track was also directed by Hiroyuki Itaya.<ref name="sony">{{cite web|url=http://www.sonymusic.co.jp/Music/Info/hiroyuki-itaya/allworks/|title=ALL WORKS {{!}} <U+677F><U+5C4B><U+5B8F><U+5E78> <U+76E3><U+7763><U+4F5C><U+54C1>|trans_title=All Works! Works directed by Hiroyuki Itaya |publisher=[[Sony Music]] Japan|language=Japanese|accessdate=May 31, 2014}}</ref> The song was used as the ending theme to the Fuji TV drama, {{nihongo|''Matsumoto Kisabur<U+014D> Ikka Monogatari: Ojisan no Daidokoro''|<U+677E><U+672C><U+559C><U+4E09><U+90CE><U+4E00><U+5BB6><U+7269><U+8A9E> <U+301C><U+304A><U+3058><U+3044><U+3055><U+3093><U+306E><U+53F0><U+6240><U+301C>||"The Story of Matsumoto Kisaburo's Family: Grandfather's Kitchen"}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvdrama-db.com/drama_info/p/id-39917|script-title=ja:<U+677E><U+672C><U+559C><U+4E09><U+90CE><U+4E00><U+5BB6><U+FF5E><U+304A><U+3058><U+3044><U+3055><U+3093><U+306E><U+53F0><U+6240><U+FF5E> - <U+30C9><U+30E9><U+30DE><U+8A73><U+7D30><U+30C7><U+30FC><U+30BF>|trans_title=Matsumoto Kisabur<U+014D> Ikka Monogatari: Ojisan no Daidokoro Drama details |publisher=TV Drama DB|language=Japanese|accessdate=May 31, 2014}}</ref>

===Reception===
While reviewing ''Cherish You'', Takayuki Saito of ''HotExpress'' magazine noted that the track has a "novel" arrangement and Matsu's current voice "calls out" to her "innocent" self of ten years ago.<ref name="hotex">{{cite web|url=http://www.hotexpress.co.jp/review/1253/|title=Cherish You {{!}} <U+677E><U+305F><U+304B><U+5B50>|work=HotExpress|publisher=Plantech Co Ltd|first=Takayuki|last=Saito|language=Japanese|accessdate=May 5, 2014}}</ref> He further commented that Matsu's voice, "full of strength", helps the listeners realize how much she has grown over the years.<ref name="hotex"/> ''CD Journal''{{'}}s reviewer wrote that the lyrics of the new version are more "positive" than the original version. They further noted that the song "overflows with adventurous spirit" woven with "nostalgia and freshness".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://artist.cdjournal.com/d/cherish-you/4107030006|title=<U+677E><U+305F><U+304B><U+5B50> / Cherish You <nowiki>[CD+DVD]</nowiki>|work=CDJournal|publisher=Ongaku Shuppansha|language=Japanese|accessdate=May 31, 2014}}</ref>

